properties.sql:
SELECT 
	customer_id as "source_customer_id",
	1 as "source_id", 
	first_name as "first_name", 
	last_name as "last_name", 
	phone as "phone", 
	email as "email", 
	date_of_birth as "date_of_birth"
FROM flowfile

SELECT 
	CAST(order_date AS VARCHAR) as "date",
	extract(year from order_date) as "year",
	extract(month from order_date) as "month",
	extract(day from order_date) as "day",
	extract(quarter from order_date) as "quarter",
	extract(dow from order_date) as "weekday",
	extract(doy from order_date) as "yearday"
FROM flowfile

SELECT 
	order_id as "source_order_id",
	1 as "source_id"
FROM flowfile

SELECT 
	product_id as "source_product_id",
	1 as "source_id", 
	product_name as "product_name", 
	price as "price"
FROM flowfile

SELECT 
	address_id as "source_address_id",
	1 as "source_id", 
	country as "country", 
	city as "city", 
	street as "street", 
	zip as "zip"
FROM flowfile

properties.SQL select query:
SELECT
    orders.order_id as "source_order_id",
    CAST(orders.order_date AS CHAR) as "order_date",
    orders.address_id as "source_address_id",
    orders.customer_id as "source_customer_id",
    order_items.product_id as "source_product_id",
    order_items.quantity as "product_quantity",
    (order_items.quantity * products.price) as "sub_price",
    SUM(order_items.quantity * products.price) OVER (PARTITION BY orders.order_id) as "total_price",
    1 as "source_id"
FROM orders
INNER JOIN order_items ON orders.order_id = order_items.order_id
INNER JOIN products ON order_items.product_id = products.product_id;
